# Mission Planer – Discord Activity

A Discord Embedded App for coordinating fleet missions with your squad in a voice channel.

## Features

- **Mission Presets** – pick from built-in missions (Recon Run, Strike Mission, Carrier Escort, Full Assault), each defining required ship types and player roles.
- **Live Ship Board** – add ships of different types; each ship type restricts which roles crew members may take.
- **Role Assignment** – click any ship to claim a role. One slot per player across all ships; re-assigning moves you automatically.
- **Goal Progress Indicator** – real-time per-ship-type and per-role progress bars that turn green when the preset's goal is fully met.
- **Session Codes** – share an 8-character code so teammates can join your planning session.
- **Multiplayer Sync** – all changes broadcast instantly via WebSocket.

## Project Structure

```
MissionPlaner/
├── shared/        # Shared TypeScript types, preset data, goal helpers
├── server/        # Express + WebSocket backend  (Node.js)
└── client/        # React + Vite frontend  (Discord Embedded App SDK)
```

## Quick Start (Local Dev)

### 1. Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- A Discord Application with the **Activities** feature enabled
  ([Developer Portal](https://discord.com/developers/applications))

### 2. Environment variables

**server/.env**
```
PORT=3001
DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=your_application_id
DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
```

**client/.env**
```
VITE_DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=your_application_id
# Optional: override the WebSocket URL (defaults to ws://localhost:3000/ws via Vite proxy)
# VITE_WS_URL=wss://your-tunnel-url/ws
```

### 3. Install & run

```bash
# From the repository root
npm install          # installs all workspace packages

# Terminal 1 – backend
cd server && npm run dev

# Terminal 2 – frontend
cd client && npm run dev
```

The client runs on **http://localhost:3000** and proxies `/api` and `/ws` to the server on port 3001.

### 4. Expose via tunnel (required for Discord Activities)

Discord requires HTTPS. Use [cloudflared](https://developers.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-one/connections/connect-networks/downloads/) or [ngrok](https://ngrok.com/):

```bash
cloudflared tunnel --url http://localhost:3000
```

Set the tunnel URL as the **URL Mapping** in your Discord Application's Activity settings.

## Data Model

| Concept | Description |
|---|---|
| `MissionPreset` | Name, description, list of `{shipType, count}` and `{role, count}` requirements |
| `ShipSlot` | A ship on the board with a type and assigned players |
| `PlayerAssignment` | A Discord user bound to a specific role on a ship |
| `MissionSession` | One planning board: a chosen preset + list of ships + host |

### Ship types and allowed roles

| Ship | Allowed Roles |
|---|---|
| Fighter | Pilot, Co-Pilot, Gunner |
| Bomber | Pilot, Co-Pilot, Bombardier, Gunner |
| Scout | Pilot, Co-Pilot, Scout, Navigator |
| Frigate | Captain, Navigator, Engineer, Gunner, Medic, Marine |
| Destroyer | Captain, Navigator, Engineer, Gunner, Medic, Marine, Technician |
| Cruiser | Captain, Navigator, Engineer, Gunner, Medic, Marine, Technician, Squadron Leader |
| Carrier | Captain, Navigator, Engineer, Medic, Technician, Squadron Leader |

## WebSocket Protocol

All real-time communication uses JSON messages over a single WebSocket connection.

**Client → Server**

| type | fields | description |
|---|---|---|
| `CREATE_SESSION` | `presetId`, `userId`, `username` | Create a new planning session |
| `JOIN` | `sessionId`, `userId`, `username` | Join an existing session by code |
| `ADD_SHIP` | `sessionId`, `shipType`, `shipName` | Add a ship to the board |
| `REMOVE_SHIP` | `sessionId`, `shipId` | Remove a ship (host only enforced client-side) |
| `ASSIGN_ROLE` | `sessionId`, `shipId`, `role`, `userId`, `username` | Claim a role on a ship |
| `UNASSIGN_ROLE` | `sessionId`, `shipId`, `userId` | Leave a ship |
| `GET_STATE` | `sessionId` | Request current session state |

**Server → Client**

| type | fields |
|---|---|
| `SESSION_CREATED` | `session` |
| `SESSION_STATE` | `session` |
| `ERROR` | `message` |

## Build

```bash
# Type-check all packages
cd shared && npx tsc
cd server && npx tsc --noEmit
cd client && npx tsc --noEmit

# Production build
cd client && npm run build
```
